,Recommended,428080,29877751,Posted: 12 February,all,plgod,"I feel like VR has a lot of people writing their first Steam review. Well it's my turn now.As VR users know, most content right now relies on the ""WOW!"" factor to be appealing, and games that are still actually fun once the VR magic fades are few and far in between. Racket: Nx is one of the only VR games I played (my VR collection has ~40 games) that is genuinely fun.IMO, this is largely due to the ""power shot"" mechanics. By hitting the ball hard, it is possible to hit many tiles in a line, while the direction of that line depends on the shot's angle and spin. The concept is simple, but being able to hit hard while controlling both aim and spin requires a lot of practice. Very few VR games require any skill from the player, but this element of skill/mastery is what makes most games fun: sports, FPS, RTS, they all get more fun as you play and become better at them.However, because of that, it might not suit everyone's taste. Fortunately there's a demo, so you can see exactly what the game is like. You get more game modes (including multiplayer) in the full game, but you won't need that to see whether you like the game or not.Definitely do try out the demo, this game is what I'm expecting from VR in the next few years."
